        "# Conclusion\n",
        "\n",
        "paragraph 1: summary of the analysis that was done\n",
        "\n",
        "paragraph 2: limitations, direction for future analysis, wrap up sentence\n",
        "\n",
        "Limitations:\n",
        "Potentially benchmarking limitations. We would like to include more covariates such as heartrate and sleep. We ran into a limitation with pypomp that it doesn't easily support different feature sets for different participants, but mathematically a pomp model could do this and it would be useful here. We would like to model the measurement distribution for all three devices, because some users use multiple devices, and leveraging them jointly would be good. Participant clustering to pool parameters for participants who are similar (such as people who have similar sleep schedules). Models we didn't get to try. How much masking affects performance. Different ways of doing masking (contiguous, across whole days, totally random, etc).\n",
