        "## Data Sources and Transformations\n",
        "\n",
        "This project uses 2024 Intern Health Study (IHS) data provided by group member [insert Drew's group member number], who is currently conducting research on this topic.\n",
        "\n",
        "The following data files were used for this project:\n",
        "\n",
        "* FitbitHourly.csv\n",
        "    + PARTICIPANTIDENTIFIER: unique ID for each doctor that participated in the study\n",
        "    + STUDY_USER_ID: study-specific unique ID for each participant\n",
        "    + time_utc: local time\n",
        "      + date_utc: local date\n",
        "      + hour_of_day_utc: local hour (0-23)\n",
        "    + For Apple, Fitbit, and Garmin, the following data was recorded.\n",
        "      + Steps: observed (recorded) step count during that hour (blank if no data was collected)\n",
        "      + StepsMissing: binary indicator of whether data was collected for step count during that hour (1 = no data, 0 = data collected)\n",
        "      + HRAvg: average heart rate during that hour\n",
        "      + HRMin: minimum heart rate during that hour\n",
        "      + HRMax: maximum heart rate during that hour\n",
        "      + HRMissing: binary indicator of whether data was collected for heart rate during that hour (1 = no data, 0 = data collected)\n",
        "      + HRVAvg: average heart rate variability during that hour\n",
        "      + HRVMissing: binary indicator of whether data was collected for heart rate variability during that hour (1 = no data, 0 = data collected)\n",
        "      + SleepMinutes: observed (recorded) minutes of sleep during that hour (blank if no data was collected)\n",
        "      + SleepMissing: binary indicator of whether data was collected for sleep during that hour (1 = no data, 0 = data collected)\n",
        "    + moodScore: scores range from 0 to 10 based on a survey\n",
        "    + messageSent: binary indicator of whether the agent sent the participant a message during that hour (1 = message was sent, 0 = no message was sent)\n",
        "    + messageStrategy: NOT SURE\n",
        "\n",
